44// Used by histograms. Values of entries should not be changed.
45enum HistogramCodecType {
46 kVideoUnknown = 0,
47 kVideoVp8 = 1,
48 kVideoVp9 = 2,
49 kVideoH264 = 3,
50 kVideoMax = 64,

54const char* kScreenPrefix = "WebRTC.Video.Screenshare.";

56const char* GetUmaPrefix(VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType content_type) {
57 switch (content_type) {
58 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kRealtimeVideo:
59 return kRealtimePrefix;
60 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen:
61 return kScreenPrefix;
62 }
63 RTC_NOTREACHED();
64 return nullptr;
65}

67HistogramCodecType PayloadNameToHistogramCodecType(
68 const std::string& payload_name) {
69 VideoCodecType codecType = PayloadStringToCodecType(payload_name);
70 switch (codecType) {
71 case kVideoCodecVP8:
72 return kVideoVp8;
73 case kVideoCodecVP9:
74 return kVideoVp9;
75 case kVideoCodecH264:
76 return kVideoH264;
77 default:
78 return kVideoUnknown;
79 }
80}

82void UpdateCodecTypeHistogram(const std::string& payload_name) {
83 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.Video.Encoder.CodecType",
84 PayloadNameToHistogramCodecType(payload_name),
85 kVideoMax);
86}

88bool IsForcedFallbackPossible(const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_info,
89 int simulcast_index) {
90 return codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 && simulcast_index == 0 &&
91 (codec_info->codecSpecific.VP8.temporalIdx == 0 ||
92 codec_info->codecSpecific.VP8.temporalIdx == kNoTemporalIdx);
93}

95absl::optional<int> GetFallbackMaxPixels(const std::string& group) {
96 if (group.empty())
97 return absl::nullopt;
98
99 int min_pixels;
100 int max_pixels;
101 int min_bps;
102 if (sscanf(group.c_str(), "-%d,%d,%d", &min_pixels, &max_pixels, &min_bps) !=
103 3) {
104 return absl::optional<int>();
105 }
106
107 if (min_pixels <= 0 || max_pixels <= 0 || max_pixels < min_pixels)
108 return absl::optional<int>();
109
110 return absl::optional<int>(max_pixels);
111}
112
113absl::optional<int> GetFallbackMaxPixelsIfFieldTrialEnabled() {
114 std::string group =
115 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kVp8ForcedFallbackEncoderFieldTrial);
116 return (absl::StartsWith(group, "Enabled"))
117 ? GetFallbackMaxPixels(group.substr(7))
118 : absl::optional<int>();
119}
120
121absl::optional<int> GetFallbackMaxPixelsIfFieldTrialDisabled() {
122 std::string group =
123 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kVp8ForcedFallbackEncoderFieldTrial);
124 return (absl::StartsWith(group, "Disabled"))
125 ? GetFallbackMaxPixels(group.substr(8))
126 : absl::optional<int>();
127}

198void SendStatisticsProxy::UmaSamplesContainer::InitializeBitrateCounters(
199 const VideoSendStream::Stats& stats) {
200 for (const auto& it : stats.substreams) {
201 uint32_t ssrc = it.first;
202 total_byte_counter_.SetLast(it.second.rtp_stats.transmitted.TotalBytes(),
203 ssrc);
204 padding_byte_counter_.SetLast(it.second.rtp_stats.transmitted.padding_bytes,
205 ssrc);
206 retransmit_byte_counter_.SetLast(
207 it.second.rtp_stats.retransmitted.TotalBytes(), ssrc);
208 fec_byte_counter_.SetLast(it.second.rtp_stats.fec.TotalBytes(), ssrc);
209 switch (it.second.type) {
210 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
211 media_byte_counter_.SetLast(it.second.rtp_stats.MediaPayloadBytes(),
212 ssrc);
213 break;
214 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
215 rtx_byte_counter_.SetLast(it.second.rtp_stats.transmitted.TotalBytes(),
216 ssrc);
217 break;
218 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
219 break;
220 }
221 }
222}

224void SendStatisticsProxy::UmaSamplesContainer::RemoveOld(int64_t now_ms) {
225 while (!encoded_frames_.empty()) {
226 auto it = encoded_frames_.begin();
227 if (now_ms - it->second.send_ms < kMaxEncodedFrameWindowMs)
228 break;
229
230 // Use max per timestamp.
231 sent_width_counter_.Add(it->second.max_width);
232 sent_height_counter_.Add(it->second.max_height);
233
234 // Check number of encoded streams per timestamp.
235 if (num_streams_ > static_cast<size_t>(it->second.max_simulcast_idx)) {
236 if (num_streams_ > 1) {
237 int disabled_streams =
238 static_cast<int>(num_streams_ - 1 - it->second.max_simulcast_idx);
239 // Can be limited in resolution or framerate.
240 uint32_t pixels = it->second.max_width * it->second.max_height;
241 bool bw_limited_resolution =
242 disabled_streams > 0 && pixels < num_pixels_highest_stream_;
243 bw_limited_frame_counter_.Add(bw_limited_resolution);
244 if (bw_limited_resolution) {
245 bw_resolutions_disabled_counter_.Add(disabled_streams);
246 }
247 }
248 }
249 encoded_frames_.erase(it);
250 }
251}

253bool SendStatisticsProxy::UmaSamplesContainer::InsertEncodedFrame(
254 const EncodedImage& encoded_frame,
255 int simulcast_idx) {
256 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
257 RemoveOld(now_ms);
258 if (encoded_frames_.size() > kMaxEncodedFrameMapSize) {
259 encoded_frames_.clear();
260 }
261
262 // Check for jump in timestamp.
263 if (!encoded_frames_.empty()) {
264 uint32_t oldest_timestamp = encoded_frames_.begin()->first;
265 if (ForwardDiff(oldest_timestamp, encoded_frame.Timestamp()) >
266 kMaxEncodedFrameTimestampDiff) {
267 // Gap detected, clear frames to have a sequence where newest timestamp
268 // is not too far away from oldest in order to distinguish old and new.
269 encoded_frames_.clear();
270 }
271 }
272
273 auto it = encoded_frames_.find(encoded_frame.Timestamp());
274 if (it == encoded_frames_.end()) {
275 // First frame with this timestamp.
276 encoded_frames_.insert(
277 std::make_pair(encoded_frame.Timestamp(),
278 Frame(now_ms, encoded_frame._encodedWidth,
279 encoded_frame._encodedHeight, simulcast_idx)));
280 sent_fps_counter_.Add(1);
281 return true;
282 }
283
284 it->second.max_width =
285 std::max(it->second.max_width, encoded_frame._encodedWidth);
286 it->second.max_height =
287 std::max(it->second.max_height, encoded_frame._encodedHeight);
288 it->second.max_simulcast_idx =
289 std::max(it->second.max_simulcast_idx, simulcast_idx);
290 return false;
291}

293void SendStatisticsProxy::UmaSamplesContainer::UpdateHistograms(
294 const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
295 const VideoSendStream::Stats& current_stats) {
296 RTC_DCHECK(uma_prefix_ == kRealtimePrefix || uma_prefix_ == kScreenPrefix);
297 const int kIndex = uma_prefix_ == kScreenPrefix ? 1 : 0;
298 const int kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples = 6;
299 char log_stream_buf[8 * 1024];
300 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder log_stream(log_stream_buf);
301 int in_width = input_width_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
302 int in_height = input_height_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
303 if (in_width != -1) {
304 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "InputWidthInPixels",
305 in_width);
306 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "InputHeightInPixels",
307 in_height);
308 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "InputWidthInPixels " << in_width << "\n"
309 << uma_prefix_ << "InputHeightInPixels " << in_height << "\n";
310 }
311 AggregatedStats in_fps = input_fps_counter_.GetStats();
312 if (in_fps.num_samples >= kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
313 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "InputFramesPerSecond",
314 in_fps.average);
315 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "InputFramesPerSecond " << in_fps.ToString()
316 << "\n";
317 }
318
319 int sent_width = sent_width_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
320 int sent_height = sent_height_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
321 if (sent_width != -1) {
322 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SentWidthInPixels",
323 sent_width);
324 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SentHeightInPixels",
325 sent_height);
326 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "SentWidthInPixels " << sent_width << "\n"
327 << uma_prefix_ << "SentHeightInPixels " << sent_height << "\n";
328 }
329 AggregatedStats sent_fps = sent_fps_counter_.GetStats();
330 if (sent_fps.num_samples >= kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
331 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SentFramesPerSecond",
332 sent_fps.average);
333 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "SentFramesPerSecond " << sent_fps.ToString()
334 << "\n";
335 }
336
337 if (in_fps.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples &&
338 sent_fps.num_samples >= kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
339 int in_fps_avg = in_fps.average;
340 if (in_fps_avg > 0) {
341 int sent_fps_avg = sent_fps.average;
342 int sent_to_in_fps_ratio_percent =
343 (100 * sent_fps_avg + in_fps_avg / 2) / in_fps_avg;
344 // If reported period is small, it may happen that sent_fps is larger than
345 // input_fps briefly on average. This should be treated as 100% sent to
346 // input ratio.
347 if (sent_to_in_fps_ratio_percent > 100)
348 sent_to_in_fps_ratio_percent = 100;
349 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(kIndex,
350 uma_prefix_ + "SentToInputFpsRatioPercent",
351 sent_to_in_fps_ratio_percent);
352 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "SentToInputFpsRatioPercent "
353 << sent_to_in_fps_ratio_percent << "\n";
354 }
355 }
356
357 int encode_ms = encode_time_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
358 if (encode_ms != -1) {
359 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "EncodeTimeInMs",
360 encode_ms);
361 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "EncodeTimeInMs " << encode_ms << "\n";
362 }
363 int key_frames_permille =
364 key_frame_counter_.Permille(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
365 if (key_frames_permille != -1) {
366 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "KeyFramesSentInPermille",
367 key_frames_permille);
368 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "KeyFramesSentInPermille "
369 << key_frames_permille << "\n";
370 }
371 int quality_limited =
372 quality_limited_frame_counter_.Percent(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
373 if (quality_limited != -1) {
374 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(kIndex,
375 uma_prefix_ + "QualityLimitedResolutionInPercent",
376 quality_limited);
377 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "QualityLimitedResolutionInPercent "
378 << quality_limited << "\n";
379 }
380 int downscales = quality_downscales_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
381 if (downscales != -1) {
382 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_ENUMERATION(
383 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "QualityLimitedResolutionDownscales", downscales,
384 20);
385 }
386 int cpu_limited =
387 cpu_limited_frame_counter_.Percent(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
388 if (cpu_limited != -1) {
389 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(
390 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "CpuLimitedResolutionInPercent", cpu_limited);
391 }
392 int bw_limited =
393 bw_limited_frame_counter_.Percent(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
394 if (bw_limited != -1) {
395 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(
396 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "BandwidthLimitedResolutionInPercent",
397 bw_limited);
398 }
399 int num_disabled =
400 bw_resolutions_disabled_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
401 if (num_disabled != -1) {
402 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_ENUMERATION(
403 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "BandwidthLimitedResolutionsDisabled",
404 num_disabled, 10);
405 }
406 int delay_ms = delay_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
407 if (delay_ms != -1)
408 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SendSideDelayInMs",
409 delay_ms);
410
411 int max_delay_ms = max_delay_counter_.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
412 if (max_delay_ms != -1) {
413 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SendSideDelayMaxInMs",
414 max_delay_ms);
415 }
416
417 for (const auto& it : qp_counters_) {
418 int qp_vp8 = it.second.vp8.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
419 if (qp_vp8 != -1) {
420 int spatial_idx = it.first;
421 if (spatial_idx == -1) {
422 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp8",
423 qp_vp8);
424 } else if (spatial_idx == 0) {
425 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp8.S0",
426 qp_vp8);
427 } else if (spatial_idx == 1) {
428 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp8.S1",
429 qp_vp8);
430 } else if (spatial_idx == 2) {
431 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp8.S2",
432 qp_vp8);
433 } else {
434 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
435 << "QP stats not recorded for VP8 spatial idx " << spatial_idx;
436 }
437 }
438 int qp_vp9 = it.second.vp9.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
439 if (qp_vp9 != -1) {
440 int spatial_idx = it.first;
441 if (spatial_idx == -1) {
442 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_500(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp9",
443 qp_vp9);
444 } else if (spatial_idx == 0) {
445 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_500(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp9.S0",
446 qp_vp9);
447 } else if (spatial_idx == 1) {
448 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_500(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp9.S1",
449 qp_vp9);
450 } else if (spatial_idx == 2) {
451 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_500(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.Vp9.S2",
452 qp_vp9);
453 } else {
454 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
455 << "QP stats not recorded for VP9 spatial layer " << spatial_idx;
456 }
457 }
458 int qp_h264 = it.second.h264.Avg(kMinRequiredMetricsSamples);
459 if (qp_h264 != -1) {
460 int spatial_idx = it.first;
461 if (spatial_idx == -1) {
462 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.H264",
463 qp_h264);
464 } else if (spatial_idx == 0) {
465 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.H264.S0",
466 qp_h264);
467 } else if (spatial_idx == 1) {
468 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.H264.S1",
469 qp_h264);
470 } else if (spatial_idx == 2) {
471 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_200(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoded.Qp.H264.S2",
472 qp_h264);
473 } else {
474 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
475 << "QP stats not recorded for H264 spatial idx " << spatial_idx;
476 }
477 }
478 }
479
480 if (first_rtp_stats_time_ms_ != -1) {
481 quality_adapt_timer_.Stop(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
482 int64_t elapsed_sec = quality_adapt_timer_.total_ms / 1000;
483 if (elapsed_sec >= metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds) {
484 int quality_changes = current_stats.number_of_quality_adapt_changes -
485 start_stats_.number_of_quality_adapt_changes;
486 // Only base stats on changes during a call, discard initial changes.
487 int initial_changes =
488 initial_quality_changes_.down + initial_quality_changes_.up;
489 if (initial_changes <= quality_changes)
490 quality_changes -= initial_changes;
491 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(kIndex,
492 uma_prefix_ + "AdaptChangesPerMinute.Quality",
493 quality_changes * 60 / elapsed_sec);
494 }
495 cpu_adapt_timer_.Stop(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
496 elapsed_sec = cpu_adapt_timer_.total_ms / 1000;
497 if (elapsed_sec >= metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds) {
498 int cpu_changes = current_stats.number_of_cpu_adapt_changes -
499 start_stats_.number_of_cpu_adapt_changes;
500 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(kIndex,
501 uma_prefix_ + "AdaptChangesPerMinute.Cpu",
502 cpu_changes * 60 / elapsed_sec);
503 }
504 }
505
506 if (first_rtcp_stats_time_ms_ != -1) {
507 int64_t elapsed_sec =
508 (clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() - first_rtcp_stats_time_ms_) / 1000;
509 if (elapsed_sec >= metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds) {
510 int fraction_lost = report_block_stats_.FractionLostInPercent();
511 if (fraction_lost != -1) {
512 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(
513 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "SentPacketsLostInPercent", fraction_lost);
514 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "SentPacketsLostInPercent "
515 << fraction_lost << "\n";
516 }
517
518 // The RTCP packet type counters, delivered via the
519 // RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver interface, are aggregates over the entire
520 // life of the send stream and are not reset when switching content type.
521 // For the purpose of these statistics though, we want new counts when
522 // switching since we switch histogram name. On every reset of the
523 // UmaSamplesContainer, we save the initial state of the counters, so that
524 // we can calculate the delta here and aggregate over all ssrcs.
525 RtcpPacketTypeCounter counters;
526 for (uint32_t ssrc : rtp_config.ssrcs) {
527 auto kv = current_stats.substreams.find(ssrc);
528 if (kv == current_stats.substreams.end())
529 continue;
530
531 RtcpPacketTypeCounter stream_counters =
532 kv->second.rtcp_packet_type_counts;
533 kv = start_stats_.substreams.find(ssrc);
534 if (kv != start_stats_.substreams.end())
535 stream_counters.Subtract(kv->second.rtcp_packet_type_counts);
536
537 counters.Add(stream_counters);
538 }
539 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex,
540 uma_prefix_ + "NackPacketsReceivedPerMinute",
541 counters.nack_packets * 60 / elapsed_sec);
542 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex,
543 uma_prefix_ + "FirPacketsReceivedPerMinute",
544 counters.fir_packets * 60 / elapsed_sec);
545 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex,
546 uma_prefix_ + "PliPacketsReceivedPerMinute",
547 counters.pli_packets * 60 / elapsed_sec);
548 if (counters.nack_requests > 0) {
549 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(
550 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "UniqueNackRequestsReceivedInPercent",
551 counters.UniqueNackRequestsInPercent());
552 }
553 }
554 }
555
556 if (first_rtp_stats_time_ms_ != -1) {
557 int64_t elapsed_sec =
558 (clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() - first_rtp_stats_time_ms_) / 1000;
559 if (elapsed_sec >= metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds) {
560 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "NumberOfPauseEvents",
561 target_rate_updates_.pause_resume_events);
562 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "NumberOfPauseEvents "
563 << target_rate_updates_.pause_resume_events << "\n";
564
565 int paused_time_percent =
566 paused_time_counter_.Percent(metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds * 1000);
567 if (paused_time_percent != -1) {
568 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "PausedTimeInPercent",
569 paused_time_percent);
570 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "PausedTimeInPercent "
571 << paused_time_percent << "\n";
572 }
573 }
574 }
575
576 if (fallback_info_.is_possible) {
577 // Double interval since there is some time before fallback may occur.
578 const int kMinRunTimeMs = 2 * metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds * 1000;
579 int64_t elapsed_ms = fallback_info_.elapsed_ms;
580 int fallback_time_percent = fallback_active_counter_.Percent(kMinRunTimeMs);
581 if (fallback_time_percent != -1 && elapsed_ms >= kMinRunTimeMs) {
582 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_PERCENTAGE(
583 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoder.ForcedSwFallbackTimeInPercent.Vp8",
584 fallback_time_percent);
585 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100(
586 kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "Encoder.ForcedSwFallbackChangesPerMinute.Vp8",
587 fallback_info_.on_off_events * 60 / (elapsed_ms / 1000));
588 }
589 }
590
591 AggregatedStats total_bytes_per_sec = total_byte_counter_.GetStats();
592 if (total_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
593 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "BitrateSentInKbps",
594 total_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
595 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "BitrateSentInBps "
596 << total_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
597 }
598 AggregatedStats media_bytes_per_sec = media_byte_counter_.GetStats();
599 if (media_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
600 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "MediaBitrateSentInKbps",
601 media_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
602 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "MediaBitrateSentInBps "
603 << media_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
604 }
605 AggregatedStats padding_bytes_per_sec = padding_byte_counter_.GetStats();
606 if (padding_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
607 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex,
608 uma_prefix_ + "PaddingBitrateSentInKbps",
609 padding_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
610 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "PaddingBitrateSentInBps "
611 << padding_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
612 }
613 AggregatedStats retransmit_bytes_per_sec =
614 retransmit_byte_counter_.GetStats();
615 if (retransmit_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
616 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex,
617 uma_prefix_ + "RetransmittedBitrateSentInKbps",
618 retransmit_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
619 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "RetransmittedBitrateSentInBps "
620 << retransmit_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
621 }
622 if (!rtp_config.rtx.ssrcs.empty()) {
623 AggregatedStats rtx_bytes_per_sec = rtx_byte_counter_.GetStats();
624 int rtx_bytes_per_sec_avg = -1;
625 if (rtx_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
626 rtx_bytes_per_sec_avg = rtx_bytes_per_sec.average;
627 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "RtxBitrateSentInBps "
628 << rtx_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
629 } else if (total_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
630 rtx_bytes_per_sec_avg = 0; // RTX enabled but no RTX data sent, record 0.
631 }
632 if (rtx_bytes_per_sec_avg != -1) {
633 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "RtxBitrateSentInKbps",
634 rtx_bytes_per_sec_avg * 8 / 1000);
635 }
636 }
637 if (rtp_config.flexfec.payload_type != -1 ||
638 rtp_config.ulpfec.red_payload_type != -1) {
639 AggregatedStats fec_bytes_per_sec = fec_byte_counter_.GetStats();
640 if (fec_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
641 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_10000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "FecBitrateSentInKbps",
642 fec_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
643 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "FecBitrateSentInBps "
644 << fec_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8) << "\n";
645 }
646 }
647 log_stream << "Frames encoded " << current_stats.frames_encoded << "\n"
648 << uma_prefix_ << "DroppedFrames.Capturer "
649 << current_stats.frames_dropped_by_capturer << "\n";
650 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "DroppedFrames.Capturer",
651 current_stats.frames_dropped_by_capturer);
652 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "DroppedFrames.EncoderQueue "
653 << current_stats.frames_dropped_by_encoder_queue << "\n";
654 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "DroppedFrames.EncoderQueue",
655 current_stats.frames_dropped_by_encoder_queue);
656 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "DroppedFrames.Encoder "
657 << current_stats.frames_dropped_by_encoder << "\n";
658 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "DroppedFrames.Encoder",
659 current_stats.frames_dropped_by_encoder);
660 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "DroppedFrames.Ratelimiter "
661 << current_stats.frames_dropped_by_rate_limiter << "\n";
662 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_1000(kIndex, uma_prefix_ + "DroppedFrames.Ratelimiter",
663 current_stats.frames_dropped_by_rate_limiter);
664 log_stream << uma_prefix_ << "DroppedFrames.CongestionWindow "
665 << current_stats.frames_dropped_by_congestion_window;
666
667 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << log_stream.str();
668}

699void SendStatisticsProxy::OnSuspendChange(bool is_suspended) {
700 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
701 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
702 stats_.suspended = is_suspended;
703 if (is_suspended) {
704 // Pause framerate (add min pause time since there may be frames/packets
705 // that are not yet sent).
706 const int64_t kMinMs = 500;
707 uma_container_->input_fps_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
708 uma_container_->sent_fps_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
709 // Pause bitrate stats.
710 uma_container_->total_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
711 uma_container_->media_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
712 uma_container_->rtx_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
713 uma_container_->padding_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
714 uma_container_->retransmit_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
715 uma_container_->fec_byte_counter_.ProcessAndPauseForDuration(kMinMs);
716 // Stop adaptation stats.
717 uma_container_->cpu_adapt_timer_.Stop(now_ms);
718 uma_container_->quality_adapt_timer_.Stop(now_ms);
719 } else {
720 // Start adaptation stats if scaling is enabled.
721 if (adaptation_limitations_.MaskedCpuCounts()
722 .resolution_adaptations.has_value())
723 uma_container_->cpu_adapt_timer_.Start(now_ms);
724 if (adaptation_limitations_.MaskedQualityCounts()
725 .resolution_adaptations.has_value())
726 uma_container_->quality_adapt_timer_.Start(now_ms);
727 // Stop pause explicitly for stats that may be zero/not updated for some
728 // time.
729 uma_container_->rtx_byte_counter_.ProcessAndStopPause();
730 uma_container_->padding_byte_counter_.ProcessAndStopPause();
731 uma_container_->retransmit_byte_counter_.ProcessAndStopPause();
732 uma_container_->fec_byte_counter_.ProcessAndStopPause();
733 }
734}

736VideoSendStream::Stats SendStatisticsProxy::GetStats() {
737 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
738 PurgeOldStats();
739 stats_.input_frame_rate =
740 round(uma_container_->input_frame_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate());
741 stats_.frames =
742 uma_container_->input_frame_rate_tracker_.TotalSampleCount();
743 stats_.content_type =
744 content_type_ == VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kRealtimeVideo
745 ? VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED
746 : VideoContentType::SCREENSHARE;
747 stats_.encode_frame_rate = round(encoded_frame_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate());
748 stats_.media_bitrate_bps = media_byte_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate() * 8;
749 stats_.quality_limitation_durations_ms =
750 quality_limitation_reason_tracker_.DurationsMs();
751 return stats_;
752}
753
754void SendStatisticsProxy::PurgeOldStats() {
755 int64_t old_stats_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() - kStatsTimeoutMs;
756 for (std::map<uint32_t, VideoSendStream::StreamStats>::iterator it =
757 stats_.substreams.begin();
758 it != stats_.substreams.end(); ++it) {
759 uint32_t ssrc = it->first;
760 if (update_times_[ssrc].resolution_update_ms <= old_stats_ms) {
761 it->second.width = 0;
762 it->second.height = 0;
763 }
764 }
765}
766
767VideoSendStream::StreamStats* SendStatisticsProxy::GetStatsEntry(
768 uint32_t ssrc) {
769 std::map<uint32_t, VideoSendStream::StreamStats>::iterator it =
770 stats_.substreams.find(ssrc);
771 if (it != stats_.substreams.end())
772 return &it->second;
773
774 bool is_media = rtp_config_.IsMediaSsrc(ssrc);
775 bool is_flexfec = rtp_config_.flexfec.payload_type != -1 &&
776 ssrc == rtp_config_.flexfec.ssrc;
777 bool is_rtx = rtp_config_.IsRtxSsrc(ssrc);
778 if (!is_media && !is_flexfec && !is_rtx)
779 return nullptr;
780
781 // Insert new entry and return ptr.
782 VideoSendStream::StreamStats* entry = &stats_.substreams[ssrc];
783 if (is_media) {
784 entry->type = VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia;
785 } else if (is_rtx) {
786 entry->type = VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx;
787 } else if (is_flexfec) {
788 entry->type = VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec;
789 } else {
790 RTC_NOTREACHED();
791 }
792 switch (entry->type) {
793 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
794 break;
795 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
796 entry->referenced_media_ssrc =
797 rtp_config_.GetMediaSsrcAssociatedWithRtxSsrc(ssrc);
798 break;
799 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
800 entry->referenced_media_ssrc =
801 rtp_config_.GetMediaSsrcAssociatedWithFlexfecSsrc(ssrc);
802 break;
803 }
804
805 return entry;
806}

820void SendStatisticsProxy::OnSetEncoderTargetRate(uint32_t bitrate_bps) {
821 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
822 if (uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_ms == -1 && bitrate_bps == 0)
823 return; // Start on first non-zero bitrate, may initially be zero.
824
825 int64_t now = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
826 if (uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_ms != -1) {
827 bool was_paused = stats_.target_media_bitrate_bps == 0;
828 int64_t diff_ms = now - uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_ms;
829 uma_container_->paused_time_counter_.Add(was_paused, diff_ms);
830
831 // Use last to not include update when stream is stopped and video disabled.
832 if (uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_paused_or_resumed)
833 ++uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.pause_resume_events;
834
835 // Check if video is paused/resumed.
836 uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_paused_or_resumed =
837 (bitrate_bps == 0) != was_paused;
838 }
839 uma_container_->target_rate_updates_.last_ms = now;
840
841 stats_.target_media_bitrate_bps = bitrate_bps;
842}

844void SendStatisticsProxy::UpdateEncoderFallbackStats(
845 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_info,
846 int pixels,
847 int simulcast_index) {
848 UpdateFallbackDisabledStats(codec_info, pixels, simulcast_index);
849
850 if (!fallback_max_pixels_ || !uma_container_->fallback_info_.is_possible) {
851 return;
852 }
853
854 if (!IsForcedFallbackPossible(codec_info, simulcast_index)) {
855 uma_container_->fallback_info_.is_possible = false;
856 return;
857 }
858
859 FallbackEncoderInfo* fallback_info = &uma_container_->fallback_info_;
860
861 const int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
862 bool is_active = fallback_info->is_active;
863 if (encoder_changed_) {
864 // Implementation changed.
865 const bool last_was_vp8_software =
866 encoder_changed_->previous_encoder_implementation == kVp8SwCodecName;
867 is_active = encoder_changed_->new_encoder_implementation == kVp8SwCodecName;
868 encoder_changed_.reset();
869 if (!is_active && !last_was_vp8_software) {
870 // First or not a VP8 SW change, update stats on next call.
871 return;
872 }
873 if (is_active && (pixels > *fallback_max_pixels_)) {
874 // Pixels should not be above |fallback_max_pixels_|. If above skip to
875 // avoid fallbacks due to failure.
876 fallback_info->is_possible = false;
877 return;
878 }
879 stats_.has_entered_low_resolution = true;
880 ++fallback_info->on_off_events;
881 }
882
883 if (fallback_info->last_update_ms) {
884 int64_t diff_ms = now_ms - *(fallback_info->last_update_ms);
885 // If the time diff since last update is greater than |max_frame_diff_ms|,
886 // video is considered paused/muted and the change is not included.
887 if (diff_ms < fallback_info->max_frame_diff_ms) {
888 uma_container_->fallback_active_counter_.Add(fallback_info->is_active,
889 diff_ms);
890 fallback_info->elapsed_ms += diff_ms;
891 }
892 }
893 fallback_info->is_active = is_active;
894 fallback_info->last_update_ms.emplace(now_ms);
895}
896
897void SendStatisticsProxy::UpdateFallbackDisabledStats(
898 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_info,
899 int pixels,
900 int simulcast_index) {
901 if (!fallback_max_pixels_disabled_ ||
902 !uma_container_->fallback_info_disabled_.is_possible ||
903 stats_.has_entered_low_resolution) {
904 return;
905 }
906
907 if (!IsForcedFallbackPossible(codec_info, simulcast_index) ||
908 stats_.encoder_implementation_name == kVp8SwCodecName) {
909 uma_container_->fallback_info_disabled_.is_possible = false;
910 return;
911 }
912
913 if (pixels <= *fallback_max_pixels_disabled_ ||
914 uma_container_->fallback_info_disabled_.min_pixel_limit_reached) {
915 stats_.has_entered_low_resolution = true;
916 }
917}

920 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
921 uma_container_->fallback_info_disabled_.min_pixel_limit_reached = true;
922}

924void SendStatisticsProxy::OnSendEncodedImage(
925 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
926 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_info) {
927 // Simulcast is used for VP8, H264 and Generic.
928 int simulcast_idx =
929 (codec_info && (codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 ||
930 codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecH264 ||
931 codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecGeneric))
932 ? encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(0)
933 : 0;
934
935 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
936 ++stats_.frames_encoded;
937 // The current encode frame rate is based on previously encoded frames.
938 double encode_frame_rate = encoded_frame_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate();
939 // We assume that less than 1 FPS is not a trustworthy estimate - perhaps we
940 // just started encoding for the first time or after a pause. Assuming frame
941 // rate is at least 1 FPS is conservative to avoid too large increments.
942 if (encode_frame_rate < 1.0)
943 encode_frame_rate = 1.0;
944 double target_frame_size_bytes =
945 stats_.target_media_bitrate_bps / (8.0 * encode_frame_rate);
946 // |stats_.target_media_bitrate_bps| is set in
947 // SendStatisticsProxy::OnSetEncoderTargetRate.
948 stats_.total_encoded_bytes_target += round(target_frame_size_bytes);
949 if (codec_info) {
950 UpdateEncoderFallbackStats(
951 codec_info, encoded_image._encodedWidth * encoded_image._encodedHeight,
952 simulcast_idx);
953 }
954
955 if (static_cast<size_t>(simulcast_idx) >= rtp_config_.ssrcs.size()) {
956 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encoded image outside simulcast range ("
957 << simulcast_idx << " >= " << rtp_config_.ssrcs.size()
958 << ").";
959 return;
960 }
961 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.ssrcs[simulcast_idx];
962
963 VideoSendStream::StreamStats* stats = GetStatsEntry(ssrc);
964 if (!stats)
965 return;
966 if (encoded_frame_rate_trackers_.count(simulcast_idx) == 0) {
967 encoded_frame_rate_trackers_[simulcast_idx] =
968 std::make_unique<rtc::RateTracker>(kBucketSizeMs, kBucketCount);
969 }
970 stats->encode_frame_rate =
971 encoded_frame_rate_trackers_[simulcast_idx]->ComputeRate();
972 stats->frames_encoded++;
973 stats->total_encode_time_ms += encoded_image.timing_.encode_finish_ms -
974 encoded_image.timing_.encode_start_ms;
975 // Report resolution of the top spatial layer.
976 bool is_top_spatial_layer =
977 codec_info == nullptr || codec_info->end_of_picture;
978
979 if (!stats->width || !stats->height || is_top_spatial_layer) {
980 stats->width = encoded_image._encodedWidth;
981 stats->height = encoded_image._encodedHeight;
982 update_times_[ssrc].resolution_update_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
983 }
984
985 uma_container_->key_frame_counter_.Add(encoded_image._frameType ==
986 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
987
988 if (encoded_image.qp_ != -1) {
989 if (!stats->qp_sum)
990 stats->qp_sum = 0;
991 *stats->qp_sum += encoded_image.qp_;
992
993 if (codec_info) {
994 if (codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
995 int spatial_idx = (rtp_config_.ssrcs.size() == 1) ? -1 : simulcast_idx;
996 uma_container_->qp_counters_[spatial_idx].vp8.Add(encoded_image.qp_);
997 } else if (codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
998 int spatial_idx = encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(-1);
999 uma_container_->qp_counters_[spatial_idx].vp9.Add(encoded_image.qp_);
1000 } else if (codec_info->codecType == kVideoCodecH264) {
1001 int spatial_idx = (rtp_config_.ssrcs.size() == 1) ? -1 : simulcast_idx;
1002 uma_container_->qp_counters_[spatial_idx].h264.Add(encoded_image.qp_);
1003 }
1004 }
1005 }
1006
1007 // If any of the simulcast streams have a huge frame, it should be counted
1008 // as a single difficult input frame.
1009 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcvideosenderstats-hugeframessent
1010 if (encoded_image.timing_.flags & VideoSendTiming::kTriggeredBySize) {
1011 ++stats->huge_frames_sent;
1012 if (!last_outlier_timestamp_ ||
1013 *last_outlier_timestamp_ < encoded_image.capture_time_ms_) {
1014 last_outlier_timestamp_.emplace(encoded_image.capture_time_ms_);
1015 ++stats_.huge_frames_sent;
1016 }
1017 }
1018
1019 media_byte_rate_tracker_.AddSamples(encoded_image.size());
1020
1021 if (uma_container_->InsertEncodedFrame(encoded_image, simulcast_idx)) {
1022 encoded_frame_rate_trackers_[simulcast_idx]->AddSamples(1);
1023 encoded_frame_rate_tracker_.AddSamples(1);
1024 }
1025
1026 absl::optional<int> downscales =
1027 adaptation_limitations_.MaskedQualityCounts().resolution_adaptations;
1028 stats_.bw_limited_resolution |=
1029 (downscales.has_value() && downscales.value() > 0);
1030
1031 if (downscales.has_value()) {
1032 uma_container_->quality_limited_frame_counter_.Add(downscales.value() > 0);
1033 if (downscales.value() > 0)
1034 uma_container_->quality_downscales_counter_.Add(downscales.value());
1035 }
1036}

1114void SendStatisticsProxy::OnAdaptationChanged(
1115 VideoAdaptationReason reason,
1116 const VideoAdaptationCounters& cpu_counters,
1117 const VideoAdaptationCounters& quality_counters) {
1118 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
1119
1120 MaskedAdaptationCounts receiver =
1121 adaptation_limitations_.MaskedQualityCounts();
1122 adaptation_limitations_.set_cpu_counts(cpu_counters);
1123 adaptation_limitations_.set_quality_counts(quality_counters);
1124 switch (reason) {
1125 case VideoAdaptationReason::kCpu:
1126 ++stats_.number_of_cpu_adapt_changes;
1127 break;
1128 case VideoAdaptationReason::kQuality:
1129 TryUpdateInitialQualityResolutionAdaptUp(
1130 receiver.resolution_adaptations,
1131 adaptation_limitations_.MaskedQualityCounts().resolution_adaptations);
1132 ++stats_.number_of_quality_adapt_changes;
1133 break;
1134 }
1135 UpdateAdaptationStats();
1136}
1137
1138void SendStatisticsProxy::UpdateAdaptationStats() {
1139 auto cpu_counts = adaptation_limitations_.MaskedCpuCounts();
1140 auto quality_counts = adaptation_limitations_.MaskedQualityCounts();
1141
1142 bool is_cpu_limited = cpu_counts.resolution_adaptations > 0 ||
1143 cpu_counts.num_framerate_reductions > 0;
1144 bool is_bandwidth_limited = quality_counts.resolution_adaptations > 0 ||
1145 quality_counts.num_framerate_reductions > 0 ||
1146 bw_limited_layers_ || internal_encoder_scaler_;
1147 if (is_bandwidth_limited) {
1148 // We may be both CPU limited and bandwidth limited at the same time but
1149 // there is no way to express this in standardized stats. Heuristically,
1150 // bandwidth is more likely to be a limiting factor than CPU, and more
1151 // likely to vary over time, so only when we aren't bandwidth limited do we
1152 // want to know about our CPU being the bottleneck.
1153 quality_limitation_reason_tracker_.SetReason(
1154 QualityLimitationReason::kBandwidth);
1155 } else if (is_cpu_limited) {
1156 quality_limitation_reason_tracker_.SetReason(QualityLimitationReason::kCpu);
1157 } else {
1158 quality_limitation_reason_tracker_.SetReason(
1159 QualityLimitationReason::kNone);
1160 }
1161
1162 stats_.cpu_limited_resolution = cpu_counts.resolution_adaptations > 0;
1163 stats_.cpu_limited_framerate = cpu_counts.num_framerate_reductions > 0;
1164 stats_.bw_limited_resolution = quality_counts.resolution_adaptations > 0;
1165 stats_.bw_limited_framerate = quality_counts.num_framerate_reductions > 0;
1166 // If bitrate allocator has disabled some layers frame-rate or resolution are
1167 // limited depending on the encoder configuration.
1168 if (bw_limited_layers_) {
1169 switch (content_type_) {
1170 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kRealtimeVideo: {
1171 stats_.bw_limited_resolution = true;
1172 break;
1173 }
1174 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen: {
1175 stats_.bw_limited_framerate = true;
1176 break;
1177 }
1178 }
1179 }
1180 if (internal_encoder_scaler_) {
1181 stats_.bw_limited_resolution = true;
1182 }
1183
1184 stats_.quality_limitation_reason =
1185 quality_limitation_reason_tracker_.current_reason();
1186
1187 // |stats_.quality_limitation_durations_ms| depends on the current time
1188 // when it is polled; it is updated in SendStatisticsProxy::GetStats().
1189}

1191void SendStatisticsProxy::OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
1192 const VideoCodec& codec,
1193 const VideoBitrateAllocation& allocation) {
1194 int num_spatial_layers = 0;
1195 for (int i = 0; i < kMaxSpatialLayers; i++) {
1196 if (codec.spatialLayers[i].active) {
1197 num_spatial_layers++;
1198 }
1199 }
1200 int num_simulcast_streams = 0;
1201 for (int i = 0; i < kMaxSimulcastStreams; i++) {
1202 if (codec.simulcastStream[i].active) {
1203 num_simulcast_streams++;
1204 }
1205 }
1206
1207 std::array<bool, kMaxSpatialLayers> spatial_layers;
1208 for (int i = 0; i < kMaxSpatialLayers; i++) {
1209 spatial_layers[i] = (allocation.GetSpatialLayerSum(i) > 0);
1210 }
1211
1212 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
1213
1214 bw_limited_layers_ = allocation.is_bw_limited();
1215 UpdateAdaptationStats();
1216
1217 if (spatial_layers != last_spatial_layer_use_) {
1218 // If the number of spatial layers has changed, the resolution change is
1219 // not due to quality limitations, it is because the configuration
1220 // changed.
1221 if (last_num_spatial_layers_ == num_spatial_layers &&
1222 last_num_simulcast_streams_ == num_simulcast_streams) {
1223 ++stats_.quality_limitation_resolution_changes;
1224 }
1225 last_spatial_layer_use_ = spatial_layers;
1226 }
1227 last_num_spatial_layers_ = num_spatial_layers;
1228 last_num_simulcast_streams_ = num_simulcast_streams;
1229}

1246void SendStatisticsProxy::TryUpdateInitialQualityResolutionAdaptUp(
1247 absl::optional<int> old_quality_downscales,
1248 absl::optional<int> updated_quality_downscales) {
1249 if (uma_container_->initial_quality_changes_.down == 0)
1250 return;
1251
1252 if (old_quality_downscales.has_value() &&
1253 old_quality_downscales.value() > 0 &&
1254 updated_quality_downscales.value_or(-1) <
1255 old_quality_downscales.value()) {
1256 // Adapting up in quality.
1257 if (uma_container_->initial_quality_changes_.down >
1258 uma_container_->initial_quality_changes_.up) {
1259 ++uma_container_->initial_quality_changes_.up;
1260 }
1261 }

1305void SendStatisticsProxy::DataCountersUpdated(
1306 const StreamDataCounters& counters,
1307 uint32_t ssrc) {
1308 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
1309 VideoSendStream::StreamStats* stats = GetStatsEntry(ssrc);
1310 RTC_DCHECK(stats) << "DataCountersUpdated reported for unknown ssrc " << ssrc;
1311
1312 if (stats->type == VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec) {
1313 // The same counters are reported for both the media ssrc and flexfec ssrc.
1314 // Bitrate stats are summed for all SSRCs. Use fec stats from media update.
1315 return;
1316 }
1317
1318 stats->rtp_stats = counters;
1319 if (uma_container_->first_rtp_stats_time_ms_ == -1) {
1320 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
1321 uma_container_->first_rtp_stats_time_ms_ = now_ms;
1322 uma_container_->cpu_adapt_timer_.Restart(now_ms);
1323 uma_container_->quality_adapt_timer_.Restart(now_ms);
1324 }
1325
1326 uma_container_->total_byte_counter_.Set(counters.transmitted.TotalBytes(),
1327 ssrc);
1328 uma_container_->padding_byte_counter_.Set(counters.transmitted.padding_bytes,
1329 ssrc);
1330 uma_container_->retransmit_byte_counter_.Set(
1331 counters.retransmitted.TotalBytes(), ssrc);
1332 uma_container_->fec_byte_counter_.Set(counters.fec.TotalBytes(), ssrc);
1333 switch (stats->type) {
1334 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
1335 uma_container_->media_byte_counter_.Set(counters.MediaPayloadBytes(),
1336 ssrc);
1337 break;
1338 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
1339 uma_container_->rtx_byte_counter_.Set(counters.transmitted.TotalBytes(),
1340 ssrc);
1341 break;
1342 case VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
1343 break;
1344 }
1345}
